@startuml Temperature Update Flow — MVVM KDBindings

skinparam backgroundColor #F8F9FA
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #444444
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam noteBorderColor #CCCCCC
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam shadowing false

actor        User
participant "ClimateView"     as CV   #FCE4EC
participant "ClimateViewModel" as CVM  #E8F8E8
participant "TemperatureModel\nProperty<int>" as M #EBF5FB
participant "HomeViewModel"   as HVM  #E8F8E8
participant "HomeView"        as HV   #FCE4EC

== Binding Setup  (once, during buildUi) ==

note over CV, HV #FFE082
  <b>MVVM Binding</b>
  Views subscribe to ViewModel properties.
  Each subscription returns a ConnectionHandle
  that keeps the binding alive.
end note

CV  ->  CVM : targetTemperature().valueChanged()\n.connect(callback)
CVM --> CV  : ConnectionHandle

HV  ->  HVM : targetTemperature().valueChanged()\n.connect(callback)
HVM --> HV  : ConnectionHandle

== Runtime: user increments temperature ==

User -> CV  : tap [+]
CV   -> CVM : increment()
CVM  -> M   : targetTemperature = get() + 1

group <b>Binding fires</b> — Property<int> notifies all ConnectionHandles  #FFE082

    M   --> CVM : valueChanged(21)
    CVM --> CV  : <b>bound</b> callback(21)
    CV  ->  CV  : updateTempLabel(21)

    M   --> HVM : valueChanged(21)
    HVM --> HV  : <b>bound</b> callback(21)
    HV  ->  HV  : updateTempLabel(21)\nlv_arc_set_value(21)

end

@enduml
